content:
Choose Your Routing Destination

Omni-Channel pushes work items to the right agent at the right time so that your support team can efficiently help customers with their problems. Depending on your business needs, route work to agents, skills, queues, or bots.

Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Omni-Channel is available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

Route to a Queue
Route work to queues to distribute the workload among a team of agents.
Route to a Skill
Improve the quality of customer service by automatically routing each work item to the best agent for the job. With skills-based routing, route every work item to the agent who has the right skills to solve the problem.
Route to an Agent
Route work directly to the preferred agent. For example, you can route sales calls from existing customers to their account executives.
Route to a Bot
Route conversations to an enhanced bot over enhanced Messaging channels. You can add powerful business rules to an Omni-Channel flow to send a conversation to a bot.
title: Choosing Your Routing Destination in Service Cloud
